have actual grades  currently enrolled courses would have anticipated midterm grades  The spreadsheet that is labeled rebuilding a GPA is designed to help cadets to determine what actions are needed to attain the minimum GPA and hour requirements for readmissions  Step 1   Place Credit Hours attempted from the bottom row  column 1 of the cadet s VMI transcript in cell B3  Step 2   Place Quality Points from the bottom row Column 3  of the cadet s VMI transcript in cell E3  Step 3   Classify future actions between the following categories  Repeating courses at VMI which will delete the former grade and replace the grade with the most recent grade even if the more recent grade is lower  Repeating courses away from VMI which must be approved for transfer credit before enrolling to ensure transfer credit  New courses at VMI  New course taken away from VMI which will increase hours but not GPA  Step 4   Enter proposed action based on the respective categories  Repeating courses at VMI Column A   Course Title Column B   Credit Hours Column C   Current Grade Column D   Proposed Grade Repeating courses away from VMI Column A   Course Title Column B   Credit Hours Column C   Current Grade Column D   the letter T New courses at VMI Column A   Course Title Column B   Credit Hours Column C   Not Applicable Column D   Proposed Grade New course taken away from VMI which will increase hours but not GPA  Column A   Course Title Column B   Credit Hours Column C   not applicable Column D   not applicable Excel File for GPA Computations The files can be saved to the cadet or adviser s computer for future reference or use  Col  Francis Bush Home Courses Links For My Advisees VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that deve